---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Terms';
const description = 'The agreement between you and BeyondBorderGroup when you use this site or hire one of our agencies.';
---

<Layout locale={locale} route="terms" title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title balance">Terms</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The agreement between you and BeyondBorderGroup when you use this site or hire one of our agencies.
      </p>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated 10 May 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow legal-prose">
      <h2>What BeyondBorderGroup does</h2>
      <p>
        BeyondBorderGroup Ltd, registered in Hong Kong, runs a group of cross-border agencies. We sell
        strategy, web infrastructure, social media, content production, distribution sourcing, and
        coordinated account management for brands moving across the China and West border in either
        direction. Each engagement is governed by a separate written agreement that names the agency,
        the scope, the fees, and the timeline. These site-wide terms cover everything around it.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of this site</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use beyondbordergroup.com for its intended purpose: learning about the group,
        contacting us, applying for a role. You will not scrape it, attempt to break into it, copy it
        to pass off as your own, run automated tools against it that interfere with normal use, or
        upload anything illegal through the contact form.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The site, its design, the agency logos, the writing, the photography, and the underlying code
        belong to BeyondBorderGroup Ltd or its licensors. You can read it. You can quote short passages
        with attribution and a link back. You cannot rebuild it or pass it off as your own.
      </p>
      <p>
        For client work: deliverables produced under a signed engagement transfer to the client on
        receipt of full payment, except where the engagement letter says otherwise. Background tools,
        frameworks, internal templates, and trained models we built before or alongside your project
        stay with us.
      </p>

      <h2>Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Invoices are due within 30 days of the invoice date. Past 30 days, we charge interest at 1.5%
        per month on the outstanding balance, or the legal maximum if lower. After 15 days late, we may
        pause the work; after 60 days, we may end the engagement and keep what has been paid.
      </p>

      <h2>No warranty, limited liability</h2>
      <p>
        We bring care and competence to every engagement. We do not guarantee that a site will rank,
        that a campaign will convert, that a partner will close, or that the site you are reading right
        now is bug-free. Beyond what local law forbids us from disclaiming, the site and our services
        are provided as is.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something goes wrong and we are at fault, our total liability to you is capped at the fees
        you paid for the specific engagement that caused the problem, in the twelve months before the
        claim. We are not on the hook for indirect, consequential, or lost-profit damages.
      </p>

      <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
      <p>
        Anything you tell us in confidence (strategy, financials, customer lists, unreleased product),
        we keep in confidence. Your team treats our pricing, methods, and internal documents the same
        way. Both obligations run for two years after the engagement ends, or longer when the law or a
        separate non-disclosure agreement says so.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. The Hong
        Kong courts have exclusive jurisdiction over any dispute, except where a separate written
        agreement names a different arbitral seat or forum.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms. The version on this page on the day you read it is the version that
        applies. Material changes will be flagged at the top so you can see what moved.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        BeyondBorderGroup Ltd<br />
        Hong Kong SAR<br />
        <a href="mailto:hello@beyondbordergroup.com">hello@beyondbordergroup.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    padding: clamp(5rem, 12vh, 8rem) 0 clamp(2rem, 5vh, 3.5rem);
    background: var(--bbg-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bbg-border);
  }
  .legal-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 0.5rem, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4);
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal-meta {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--bbg-text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-3);
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
  }
  .legal-prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal-prose p,
  .legal-prose ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--bbg-text);
  }
  .legal-prose ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .legal-prose li { margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--bbg-blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal-prose a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
</style>
